ta Constantin,et al.", "date": "(2006)", "journal": "Cell", "pmid": "[PMID:16873062]", "title": "Endonucleolytic function of MutLalpha in human mismatch repair.", "vol": "126(2):297-308."}, {"authors": "W Glenn McCluggage,Naveena Singh,C Blake Gilks", "date": "(2022)", "journal": "Histopathology", "pmid": "[PMID:34996131]", "title": "Key changes to the World Health Organization (WHO) classification of female genital tumours introduced in the 5th edition (2020).", "vol": "80(5):762-778."}, {"authors": "R Fishel,A Ewel,S Lee,et al.", "date": "(1994)", "journal": "Science", "pmid": "[PMID:7973733]", "title": "Binding of mismatched microsatellite DNA sequences by the human MSH2 protein.", "vol": "266(5189):1403-5."}, {"authors": "R Fishel,M K Lescoe,M R Rao,et al.", "date": "(1993)", "journal": "Cell", "pmid": "[PMID:8252616]", "title": "The human mutator gene homolog MSH2 and its association with hereditary nonpolyposis colon cancer.", "vol": "75(5):1027-38."}], "therapeutic_regimen": [{"adaptation_disease_cn": [], "adaptation_disease_en": [], "approval_organization": [], "approval_tumour": [], "drug_details": [{"dosage": "", "drug_code": "92fecd1c737811eca8e0005056bdcbf7", "drug_mechanism_cn": " CRM1 是蛋白质从细胞核到细胞质的主要输出因子，在多种癌细胞类型中过度表达。Selinexor 是一种可口服的 CRM1（染色体区域维持 1 蛋白，输出蛋白 1 或 XPO1）小分子抑制剂，具有潜在的抗肿瘤活性。 Selinexor 修饰必需的 CRM1 货物结合残基半胱氨酸 528，从而不可逆地灭活 CRM1 介导的货物蛋白核输出，例如肿瘤抑制蛋白 (TSP)，包括 p53、p21、BRCA1/2、pRB、FOXO 和其他生长调节蛋白。 因此，该药物通过选择性抑制核输出 (SINE) 的方法，恢复内源性肿瘤抑制过程，从而选择性地消除肿瘤细胞，同时保留正常细胞。", "drug_mechanism_en": "An orally available, small molecule inhibitor of CRM1 (chromosome region maintenance 1 protein, exportin 1 or XPO1), with potential antineoplastic activity. Selinexor modifies the essential CRM1-cargo binding residue cysteine-528, thereby irreversibly inactivates CRM1-mediated nuclear export of cargo proteins such as tumor suppressor proteins (TSPs), including p53, p21, BRCA1/2, pRB, FOXO, and other growth regulatory proteins. As a result, this agent, via the approach of selective inhibition of nuclear export (SINE), restores endogenous tumor suppressing processes to selectively eliminate tumor cells while sparing normal cells. CRM1, the major export factor for proteins from the nucleus to the cytoplasm, is overexpressed in a variety of cancer cell types.", "drug_name": "塞利尼索;Selinexor", "regimen_code": "aad0b446737811eca8e0005056bdcbf7"}], "drug_type": null, "regimen_alias": null, "regimen_cn": "塞利尼索", "regimen_en": "Selinexor", "regimen_mechanism_cn": null, "regimen_mechanism_en": null, "var_name": "CNL type EC", "var": [{"biomarker_type": "CNL type EC"}]}], "therapeutic_regimen_resistant": []}